The wizard Arcimus was heralded as a creative genius by some and as a lunatic by others. However, everybody agreed that Arcimus knew how to wreak havoc and devastation. 

His whereabouts and status are unknown after a strange accident that destroyed his tower, but since that time items bearing his name have appeared around the Isles. 

(Page Class)
The Great Arcimus' Lesser Boom Stick
These undead carrion eaters haunt the graveyards and battlefields that bore them, still bearing the rotting flesh they once wore in life.
These bats are vicious little bloodsuckers, with fangs sharper than the rest of their kin.
Wights are undead creatures, the remains of those that delved too far and too long into the black arts.
With red eyes and a feral visage, this creature is surely a vampire.

Universal Template for settlement Elite Guard.

You may change appearances of items or change weapon types, but make sure all items have the same properties afterward. Do not change stats on the base creature, either. This is important for fairness across the board. Do not give them any additional accessories beyond what is visible: armor, cloak, helmet, shield, weapon. They don't have to have all of these items equipped, but do not give them more than that.

Seeking weapons are the pride of those who prefer to face their enemy at a distance. Crafted of ebony and enchanted by ancient magical enhancements of the Elemental Plane of Air, these weapons cause a momentary tunnel of wind as the projectile is fired, causing the weapon to rarely miss and connect with the target at a much higher velocity.
